# React UI Rules

## Stack

- React 19 + TypeScript (new components) / JSX (legacy `App.jsx`)
- Tailwind CSS v4 — config in `src/index.css` via `@theme`
- shadcn/ui components in `src/components/ui/` (Radix primitives)

## Patterns

- Use `const handleClick = () =>` naming for event handlers
- Early returns for loading/error states
- Tailwind classes only — no separate CSS files for components
- Accessibility: `aria-label`, keyboard handlers on interactive elements

## Settings & State

- App settings: `useSettings.ts` + localStorage keys (see CLAUDE.md §5)
- Audio recording: `useAudioRecording.js`
- Hotkeys: `useHotkey.js`
- Permissions: `usePermissions.ts`

## IPC from Renderer

Access main process only via `window.api.*` (defined in `preload.js`). Never import Electron in renderer directly.

## Component Layout

- `App.jsx` — minimal overlay (recording states, drag handle)
- `ControlPanel.tsx` — tabbed settings, history, model picker
- `OnboardingFlow.tsx` — 8-step first-run wizard
- `SettingsPage.tsx` — detailed settings forms

## Styling

- `cn()` from `src/components/lib/utils.ts` for conditional classes
- Lucide React for icons
- Dark mode via Tailwind `@variant` in `index.css`
